  "prompt": "What is the dress code for fresher girls in Capgemini?",
  "response": "The dress code for fresher girls at Capgemini, like for all employees, typically follows a business casual standard. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n- **Tops:** Blouses, shirts, or tops that are modest and professional. Avoid anything too revealing or casual like tank tops or t-shirts with graphics.\n- **Bottoms:** Trousers, skirts, or dresses that are knee-length or longer. Jeans might be acceptable on certain days, but it's best to check with your specific office's policy.\n- **Shoes:** Closed-toe shoes are generally preferred. Heels should be of a reasonable height for safety and comfort.\n- **Accessories:** Keep them minimal and professional. Avoid overly flashy jewelry or accessories.\n\nIt's always a good idea to check with your HR department or refer to the company's employee handbook for the most accurate and up-to-date dress code information. Some offices may have more relaxed or stricter policies depending on their location and culture.",
